                            <comment id="17300454" author="beamjirabot" created="Fri, 12 Mar 2021 17:18:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is P2 but has been unassigned without any comment for 60 days so it has been labeled &quot;stale-P2&quot;. If this issue is still affecting you, we care! Please comment and remove the label. Otherwise, in 14 days the issue will be moved to P3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please see &lt;a href=&quot;https://beam.apache.org/contribute/jira-priorities/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://beam.apache.org/contribute/jira-priorities/&lt;/a&gt; for a detailed explanation of what these priorities mean.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17310015" author="beamjirabot" created="Sat, 27 Mar 2021 17:19:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was marked &quot;stale-P2&quot; and has not received a public comment in 14 days. It is now automatically moved to P3. If you are still affected by it, you can comment and move it back to P2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17311833" author="kenn" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2021 22:16:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If we build a docker container, could it also be used for Jenkins builds? IIRC there was a problem with this losing incremental build. But if we can integrate with an external gradle cache we&apos;d be in better shape?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17311834" author="kenn" created="Tue, 30 Mar 2021 22:17:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another option that we use for docs is the snippets mechanism. This way we could have a script we can test, and pull snippets from it into instructions if we need to give context on the instructions. (or just treat comments in the script as instructions)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17312515" author="tysonjh" created="Wed, 31 Mar 2021 16:12:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Regarding using it for Jenkins - I thought this would be a nice idea as well. TBH I&apos;m not sure of the downsides but the incremental build does sound like it would be a problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding the snippets mechanism, that would be ideal I think. Have a simple script that does everything with comments in it, show the snippets in page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the docker container image, I&apos;m not sure why the shell script &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/start-build-env.sh&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/master/start-build-env.sh&lt;/a&gt;&#160;is so complicated. IMO having a plain old Dockerfile plus some instructions on how to use it would be better. Maybe &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=emilymye&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;emilymye&quot;&gt;emilymye&lt;/a&gt;&#160;could add some thoughts here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17323888" author="isidro.martinez" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2021 15:07:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-11608&quot; title=&quot;Development environment set up automation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BEAM-11608&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BEAM-11608&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; adds the shell script and CI integration.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
